<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 02 at 10:40AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT WITH MODERATE TO
BRIEFLY HEAVY SNOW DURING LATE MORNING INTO EARLY AFTERNOON...
WEATHER...
* Moderate to briefly heavy snow continues during late morning
into early afternoon.
* Additional accumulation of 1 to 2 inches between 1030 AM and
100 PM. Localized accumulation up to 3 inches along and south
of M-46.
* Temperatures fall into the 20s during the afternoon.
IMPACTS...
* Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility for
motorists and snow covered roads.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Motorists are urged to use caution and account for the
hazardous driving conditions by allowing extra time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
